similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Tatershall , 2nd baron of Tattershall 1297-1302 was born in 1273, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Tattershall, was 25 and his mother, Joan FitzRandolph, was 24. He married Eve Tibetoft in November 1280. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1302, in his hometown, at the age of 29."},"et":{"1273 (age 24 1297)–1302":"1273–1302","1267–1310":"1267–1310","1272–1329":"1272–1329","1273–1302":"1273–1302","1272–1350":"1272–1350","1287–1310":"1287–1310","–Female":"Surnud","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1310":"1250–1310","November 1280":"november 1280","1273 (age 24 1297)":"1273","1350":"1350","1273":"1273","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","1287 (age 15 1302)":"1287","before 8 September 1298":"enne 8. septembrit 1298","1248":"1248","1302":"1302","1267":"1267","1310":"1310","1298":"1298","1287":"1287","1329":"1329","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tatershall, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1273 (age 24 1297)–1302":"1273–1302","1267–1310":"1267–1310","1272–1329":"1272–1329","1273–1302":"1273–1302","1272–1350":"1272–1350","1287–1310":"1287–1310","–Female":"Kuollut","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1310":"1250–1310","November 1280":"marraskuu 1280","1273 (age 24 1297)":"1273","1350":"1350","1273":"1273","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","1287 (age 15 1302)":"1287","before 8 September 1298":"ennen vuotta 8. syys